qoriq-rcw (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add --dump mode: read the live RCW snapshot from /dev/mem on a
    running QorIQ/Layerscape board and emit a recompilable .rcw file
    with a header documenting the detected SoC, addresses, and the
    sanity checks performed.
  * Add --dump-flash mode: read the on-flash RCW + PBI directly from
    the boot medium. Auto-detects the device from PORSR1.RCW_SRC at
    DCFG offset 0x0 and a /proc/mtd partition-name scan. Supports
    --slot primary|fallback|all (with separate output files for
    "all"), --device override, and full sanity battery (preamble,
    load_cmd, checksum, terminator, rcw_consistent vs live RCWSR,
    fallback_match across slots).
  * New qoriq-rcw-data binary package shipping the canonical .rcwi
    files vendored from nxp-qoriq/rcw.

 -- Vincent Jardin <vjardin@free.fr>  Mon, 13 Apr 2026 14:00:00 +0000

qoriq-rcw (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

